        <body>       

                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Trenton N. J. July 24. 88<lb/>
                Rev. Dr. Mora&#239;s<lb/>
                Philadelphia<lb/>
                Pa.<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear sir &#38; colleague&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>Kindly<lb/> allow me to call your<lb/> attention to a small<lb/> official matter pending<lb/> between you and me.<lb/></p>
            <p>A<lb/> certain Mr. Pardo of<lb/> this city has about a<lb/> year ago nominally<lb/> joined our Har Sina<lb/> congregation i. e. has<lb/> on his application<lb/> been elected a member<lb/> but has paid no or<lb/> almost no dues yet<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>and is&#44; as I understand<lb/> some twenty dollars&#44;<lb/> in arrear.  During<lb/> this time he certainly<lb/> would if necessary<lb/> have claimed the rights<lb/> of a member&#44; as the use<lb/> of burial ground etc.<lb/>  This he proved in following<lb/> instance.  His sister in<lb/> law&#44; who lives with him&#44;<lb/> is about to be married<lb/> and he has asked me<lb/> to give &#91;Hebrew&#93; and I<lb/> had accepted it and<lb/> therefore <sic>delaied</sic> my<lb/> departure from here as<lb/> I am to leave in order<lb/> to accept the Ministry<lb/> of  Jacksonville Fla.<lb/>  Pardo wanted the<lb/> ceremony to be performed<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>in the synagogue<lb/> and the President of this<lb/> congregation consented<lb/> to that with the condition<lb/> that he first pay his<lb/> arrear dues in order that<lb/> he be a member of<lb/> good standing.  The<lb/> next thing I heard<lb/> was&#44; that P. is about<lb/> to offer you the &#91;Hebrew&#93; to<lb/> be performed in his house.<lb/>  Of course he has a right<lb/> to that and may take<lb/> any minister he pleases<lb/> although in his house<lb/> I too would have per&#44;<lb/>formed the ceremony<lb/> without asking any<lb/> questions about congre<lb/>gational matters.  But<lb/> I trust you will neither<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="4"/>
            <p>strengthen any one<lb/> in trespassing against<lb/> the principle &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/> nor cause a colleague<lb/> to be &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/></p>
            <p>The affair is to come of<lb/> on August 26.<lb/></p>
            <p>Please excuse and accept<lb/> colleaguial greetings<lb/> of yours truly<lb/> Rev. J Kahn<lb/>
                Pennington Av. 57<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="5"/>
            <p>Rev. Dr. Morais<lb/>
                Philadelphia<lb/>
                Pa.<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="6"/>
            <p>Return to Rev. J Kahn<lb/> Trenton N. J. Pennington str. 47<lb/> if not delivered<lb/> within 5 days<lb/></p>
            </body>
